{
  "stem": "17761.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were less bad than the Germans.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But in the last few days, everybody of us wanted to have a German officer in our house, because it was a kind of a protection for drunkards or of all kind of hooligans and so on which were in the German army.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it was amazing to see, under these conditions on the ghetto, the-- the German soldiers coming with a book to read, toothpaste and the toothbrush like-- and the pajamas and all.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was amazing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But things became very hot.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And about a day earlier-- about a day early, the event I'm going to tell you, the SS came-- came in.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We know now that they had the order to exterminate the ghetto in 24 or 48 hours.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But [INAUDIBLE] Shabbat-- it was in March, 1944, but I remember it was [INAUDIBLE] Shabbat-- we heard from the loudspeakers from the bridge because the Germans-- they had there, by the way, quarrel with the Romanian.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Who says which unit will go first?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because they all run for their life.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that very loud-- strong, loud speakers, we heard that there is a lot of agitation.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My father and myself, maybe we're-- I'm not sure we were the only one but very-- from the very few-- we went on the roof of the casino up, and we watched what's going on.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was a lot of light because there were those big projectors to the bridge.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And suddenly we heard in German language, [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Ivan, that was the-- the German called the Russians Ivan, and the Russians called the German Fritz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Ivan is on the mountain.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was a mountain the side of-- that side.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The bridges will be exploding in 10 minutes.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
